Small enterprises in the import and logistics business stand to gain from the local marine cargo insurance policy which came into effect from January 1, an industry expert has said.Kenya Orient CEO Muema Muindi said the new law will significantly cut the cost of importing goods such as raw materials, vehicles and machinery.It is also expected to reduce the risks that local small and medium enterprises are exposed to when buying goods in foreign markets. &ldquo;This is good news for SMEs as they will now more easily access cargo insurance at affordable cost,&rdquo; Muindi said.